	<h1>My Favorite NBA Players Growing Up</h1>
	
	<h2>Derrick Rose<h2>
	<p> As a Chicago native, I was and still am a die hard <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Derrick_Rose"><strong>Derrick Rose</strong></a>fan. I followed Rose's journey from when he was in highschool
	at Simeon Career Academy watching highlight mixtapes on Youtube. After highschool, I watched him play a year in college at The University of Memphis in which after he entered the NBA draft and was selected
	as the Number 1 pick of the 2008 draft by the Chicago Bulls. As far as I could tell, bringing a #1 pick who was a Chicago native to the Bulls franchise was an exciting thing to say the least. As a basketball 
	fan growing up, watching D. Rose's explosiveness and agility was always exhilarating. The Bulls after the Jordan era wasn't doing too well and Derrick Rose gave the team new found hope after he decided to do
	his thing and become the league's youngest MVP at 22 years old in his 3rd season. In that same MVP year, Rose led the Bulls to the Eastern Conference Finals, in which they have not been there in years. 
	Unfortunately, they had lost to the Miami Heat led by Lebron James. This was as far Rose had gotten in the playoffs before he tragically tore his ACL the following year in the playoffs against the Philadelphia 76ers. 
	After recovering the following years, he has bounced from team to team but has worked on body recovery tremedously and has found a solid role on his current team of the New York Knicks.</p>
	
