	<h2>Dwayne Wade<h2>
	<p> Around the same time I started watching Derrick Rose, I quickly became a fan of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dwyane_Wade"><strong>Dwayne Wade</strong></a> who also is a Chicago native but was drafted 
	5th overall in 2006 by the Miami Heat. Dwayne Wade, nicknamed the "Flash" was a shifty and dominant shooting guard who won his first NBA championship in 2006 with the Miami Heat. However, I was only 6 at that time
	so the Dwayne Wade I grew up admiring was the 2008 and on version. After beating Derrick Rose and the Chicago Bulls in the 2011 Eastern Conference Finals, the Heat had advacned to the Finals where they lost 4-2 to 
	the Dallas Mavericks. After the 2011 defeat to the Mavs, Dwayne Wade and the Heat went on to win back to back championships with the help of LeBron James and Chris Bosh in 2012 and 2013. After countless All-Star
	appearances, Dwayne Wade retired as one of the greatest to do it and a Miami Heat legend in 2019.</p>
	
